public class FileAccessor
extends java.lang.Object

Implements a basic file accessor, this accessor keeps track of a single file and its metadata mappings

loadData

public void loadData()
This function assumes that all the metadata for the file has been loaded previously, we just need to retrieve the file from disk again. This is useful if we are processing massive amounts of data and only want to keep the working set of data in memory.
